name: Chase Ink
overview:
1. Chase Ink Business Unlimited®
Best For: Simplicity and flat-rate cashback.
Rewards: Earn 1.5% cashback on every purchase with no caps or category restrictions.
Annual Fee: $0.
Key Features:
Unlimited cashback makes it ideal for businesses with diverse spending.
Employee cards at no additional cost.
Fraud protection and purchase monitoring.
2. Chase Ink Business Premier®
Best For: Large-scale spending and maximizing rewards.
Rewards:
Earn 2% cashback on every purchase.
Earn 2.5% cashback on purchases of $5,000 or more.
Annual Fee: $195.
Key Features:
Ideal for businesses with significant expenditures.
Advanced reporting tools to manage expenses.
No foreign transaction fees.
lendor_requirements:
1. Business Information
Type of Business: Sole proprietorships, partnerships, LLCs, corporations, and other registered entities are eligible.
Years in Business: While startups can apply, established businesses with a track record may have an advantage.
Business Revenue: Providing accurate annual business revenue is crucial. Higher revenue may increase your likelihood of approval.
Industry Type: Chase evaluates your business risk based on your industry.
2. Personal Information
Credit Score: A good to excellent personal credit score (typically 700 or higher) significantly increases approval chances.
Personal Guarantee: Chase requires a personal guarantee, meaning the cardholder is personally responsible for debts incurred on the card.
3. Credit History
Business Credit History: If applicable, your business credit profile is considered. A strong business credit history can improve your chances.
Personal Credit History: Since business owners provide a personal guarantee, a solid personal credit history is essential.
Chase's 5/24 Rule: Chase generally denies applicants who have opened five or more personal credit cards (across all issuers) in the past 24 months.
4. Debt-to-Income Ratio
Chase may assess your ability to repay based on your personal and business debt compared to income.
5. Financial Documentation
Chase may request additional documents, such as:
Tax identification number (EIN or SSN for sole proprietors).
Business tax returns or financial statements (in rare cases).
Proof of business ownership.
6. Other Factors
Existing Relationship with Chase: Having an existing account or banking relationship with Chase can work in your favor.
Application Accuracy: Ensure all information is accurate and consistent with other business and credit records.

name: Ally
overview:
Ally offers commercial vehicle financing options designed to support both personal and business needs while reporting to business credit bureaus.
Third-Party Guarantee

If you wish to purchase or lease vehicles under your business name but require additional financing, you can act as a third-party guarantor. This arrangement keeps your name off the vehicle title and may prevent the debt from appearing on your personal credit record. However, if your business defaults, you may become personally liable, and the debt could be reported on your personal credit record.
Business Name Only Financing

If your business qualifies without the need for an owner's guarantee, financing can be secured exclusively in the business name. This approach allows you to:

    Build credit in your business name.
    Protect your personal credit for other financial needs.
    Shield yourself from liability related to the operation of the vehicle.

Ally's flexible financing solutions are tailored to help businesses grow while safeguarding owners' personal financial standing.Ally offers commercial vehicle financing options designed to support both personal and business needs while reporting to business credit bureaus.
